import React, { useEffect } from 'react' /** * @author * @function Datacapture **/ const Datacapture = (props) => { let points = null useEffect(() => { points = localStorage.getItem('points') }, []) const on_submit = (e) => { e.preventDefault() console.log(`Fullname: ${e.target.fullname.value} | Email: ${e.target.email.value} | Company: ${e.target.company.value}`) } return (

{`CONGRATULATIONS! YOU GOT ${points}/5 ANSWERS CORRECT!`}

Enter your contact info for a chance to win your Dirty-Laundry Collection!

) } export default Datacapture
